article.help
  .container-fluid
    section.row-fluid.summary
      .summary.col-sm-3
        h3 DELETE
        p.lead Delete nodes or relationships
      .details.col-sm-9
        p
          | The&nbsp;
          code DELETE
          |  clause is used to delete nodes and relationships
          | identified within a&nbsp;
          code MATCH
          |  clause, possibly qualified by a&nbsp;
          code WHERE
          | . Remember that you can not delete a node 
          | without also deleting relationships that start or end on said node.
        table.table-condensed.table-help
          tr
            th Reference:
            td
              code
                a(href='http://neo4j.com/docs/{{neo4j.version}}/query-delete.html') DELETE
              |  manual page
          tr
            th Related:
            td
              a(help-topic='detach-delete') :help DETACH DELETE
              | &nbsp;
              a(help-topic='match') :help MATCH
              | &nbsp;
              a(help-topic='where') :help WHERE
              | &nbsp;
              a(help-topic='remove') :help REMOVE
              | &nbsp;
              a(help-topic='cypher') :help Cypher
    section.row-fluid.example
      .col-sm-9.col-sm-offset-3
        figure
          pre.code.runnable.
            MATCH (n)-[r]-() WHERE n.name = 'Soren' DELETE r
          figcaption Remove all of Soren's friends.
